Since Moodle 1.6 it is possible to redirect students to a course hosted on an external server . Looking at the code in `course/view.php` , I notice the following comment: 
```text
//If course is hosted on an external server, redirect to corresponding
//url with appropriate authentication attached as parameter
```
 I am able to add the externserver.php file with the relevant function, but I can't figure out how one could add the authentication as a parameter. I would like people authenticated on one Moodle server to be logged in on the redirect server as well. How can this be done?

I've seen a couple of indications that logoutpage_hook (in an authentication plugin's auth.php) should verify that the user is using the current authentication plugin before doing things like a redirect. 
```text
if ($USER->auth === $this->authtype) {


global $USER; // use $USER->auth to find the plugin used for login


global $redirect; // can be used to override redirect after logout


// do things


}
```
 Is this actually necessary?  If so, why?  Doesn't Moodle already know which authentication plugin the user is using?  Thanks!

You can achieve this with a small code modification. Edit lib/moodlelib.php and inside function authenticate_user_loging(), around line 3223 (for 1.9.14+, may vary a little for 1.9.4, you'll see a piece of code like this: 
```text




        } else {



            // if user not found, create him



            $user = create_user_record($username, $password, $auth);



        }
```
 You need to change it to look like this; 
```text




        } else {



            // if user not found, do *not* create him



            continue;



        }
```

